commitResults.messageTitle: Level 0: Greet Implements an initial skeletal version of Duke that simply greets the user and exits.
Level 1: Greet, Echo, Exit Implement a skeletal version of Duke that starts by greeting the user, simply echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types bye.
Level 2: Add, List Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.
Level 3: Mark as Done Add the ability to mark tasks as done. Optionally, add the ability to change the status back to not done.
A-CodingStandard: Follow the Coding Standard Tweak the code to comply with a given coding standard.
Level-4: ToDos, Events, Deadlines Add support for tracking three types of tasks:
commitResults.messageBody:
ToDos: tasks without any date/time attached to it e.g., visit new theme park
Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time e.g., submit report by 11/10/2019 5pm
Events: tasks that start at a specific time and ends at a specific time e.g., team project meeting on 2/10/2019 2-4pm
